Cornell Says Long-Term Investments Rose 20% in Year Ended June

-- B y   G i l l i a n   W e e
-- 
2011-09-28T17:07:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/cornell-says-long-term-investments-rose-20-in-year-ended-june.html
Cornell University  said its long-
term investments rose 20 percent in the 12 months ended June 30.  The value of long-term investments climbed to $5.35
billion, according to an e-mailed statement today from Claudia
Wheatley, a university spokeswoman.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gillian Wee in  New York  at 
 gwee3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christian Baumgaertel at 
 cbaumgaertel@bloomberg.net . 